Life Line Screening

Life Line Screening

Nearby Screening Alert

Practical prevention for adults 40+

Take charge before symptoms appear

Annual cardiovascular and chronic disease screening packages help make early detection easier—with fast, non-invasive testing and appointment options near you.

Screening package focus

Reviews for stroke risk, vascular health, and chronic disease indicators

Designed for women 40+, men 40+, and all adults 40+ seeking a simpler, credible way to stay ahead of risk.

• Carotid artery screening

• Peripheral arterial disease (PAD) screening

• Abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) screening

• Atrial fibrillation screening

Why book now

Trusted by over 10 million customers

With 14,000+ U.S. screening locations, it’s easier to find a date and site that works for your schedule.

Results are typically available online in about 10 days.

What makes it practical

Comfortable visit

Fast, painless, and non-invasive appointments designed to fit into everyday life.

Local access

Community screening events may be available near you, making booking simpler and more convenient.

Clear follow-up

Online results help support informed next steps and more confident conversations about health.

Why many adults 40+ choose Life Line Screening

“The process felt quick and straightforward, and the results helped me feel more informed.”

“It was reassuring to find a location nearby and get screenings done without a complicated appointment.”

Recognized by millions of customers and commonly featured in trusted news and consumer conversations about preventive screening.

Find a Screening Near You

Life Line Screening exists to make preventive health screening more approachable for adults who want clarity before symptoms disrupt daily life. The annual cardiovascular and chronic disease screening packages are built around that simple goal: offer practical access to information that can support timely, informed decisions.

The brand’s approach centers on convenience and reassurance rather than alarm. By focusing on screening options near where people live, straightforward appointment experiences, and clear online result delivery, Life Line Screening helps make regular health review feel manageable instead of overwhelming.

For adults 40+, that mission matters. Stroke risk tests and vascular screenings can be easier to fit into a routine when the process is fast, non-invasive, and credible. Life Line Screening keeps the emphasis on helping people stay proactive, informed, and confident about their next step.

Screening packages vary by selection and availability. This message is intended for U.S. adults interested in preventive health screening, especially those age 40 and older.

